article_title: Pedestrian killed while crossing Kansas highway
article_text:
Authorities say a pedestrian has died while crossing a highway near the northeast Kansas town of Bonner Springs.

The Kansas Highway Patrol says a vehicle collided with the victim just before 1 a.m. Sunday at the intersection of Kansas 7 and 130th Street. The driver stopped and was questioned.

No other information was immediately available, including the name of the victim.
